The article discusses the nominations sent to the Senate on Thursday, January 13, 2022. The nominations include Sarah Bloom Raskin from Maryland, who has been nominated to be a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System for the unexpired term of fourteen years from February 1, 2018, replacing Randal Quarles, who resigned. Raskin has also been nominated to be Vice Chairman for Supervision of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System for a term of four years, replacing Randal Quarles. 

Lisa DeNell Cook from Michigan has been nominated to be a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System for the unexpired term of fourteen years from February 1, 2010, replacing Janet L. Yellen, who resigned. 

Philip Nathan Jefferson from North Carolina has been nominated to be a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System for a term of fourteen years from February 1, 2022, replacing Richard Clarida, who resigned.